spanGrp.span: Today at some point I saw something in something;
Jirda ys t mgal (_) s-ra-m jele jrga
what I saw when I watched it was that first a man appeared with something white around his head.
Ji (_) s'-je n je r nmga s'-je-n-ra s sgtran pekaga desu tsagu pabt-l wa r surrun
He was shaking something outside the house.
Je t jir wkbe-g-n j shebega bi
Inside the house there was a girl sitting;
Ta j jrga n ra pebusi kajkiri n
she had a child lying down on a nice bench they had made.
je w yaba jie-l-w-n kalwak n (_) yulei w b ram jrga
She left him alone and went out with her husband.
jawatan-ite eglaua (m) Ta jie jk yas' j shebega juape ra
Where they went I dont know.
Mga mnu-lo ka juen s-w inga
They thought the child was asleep; so, they left him sleeping while they went for a walk, maybe.
Je begets yaba kap-w jetan-ite kp mientras ke jie-wa m-gu-lo-m yul le
Meanwhile I see that two little pacas came to where the child was sleeping.
Je deleigara ys s-ra komo kono bi yabla bi (_) deu-lo bo-l m yaba kablali kp ska
I thought they were going to devour or frighten him,
begets ys kete-g-w-ite le o mleche-g-ite r
But it was not like that.
but they woke him up and the child got up and they went before him, so chased them;
shki-w-ka-ite yaba jk kag Kepa mnu-lo-ka alawtso alawtso tjiu-m-ite
They got to a huge place with lots of nice trees and flowers;
mnu-lo-ka kal sigen k b ram Pe mamaw juer b ram
The child chased them and they were ahead.
Yaba t tjiu-m tjiu-m jie-wa julur-gate alawtsoka
The childs shirt got stuck on a tree; it tore apart;
Yaba pagl jienawatan-n kal bata m Kashanu-m
he screamed at them, but they would not listen to him.
je r-g-n tsagara ka wakwa t kuge
Next, there appeared a fucking snake;
Jekepa (_) (_) jeskan mga kaljula jrga keb chi tsn-te-n (_)
it rolled over the child with its tail all the way up to his neck.
Je t yaba pabotr-w-n mlek wa butr-w-ite k degu kuli ska (_)
The child opened its mouth, but I dont believe that;
Yaba t k jakke-g-n ka s-w je kgan
No child could ever open a snakes mouth like that!
Jir keb (_) k jakke yabla t je bi n
How come it didnt bite him, if he pulled out its tongue all the way?
Mnbi ka w kunn n K jakk-ite jekepa kkt y-ite bets (_)
There the snake got mad and threw the child down to the ground and he went up to another tree.
Jeskanra keb ulun' t yaba bu-m-n jiski inga (_) Jk pakk-s'-n kal kww jrga n
There he lost sight of the ones who took him there [the pacas].
Jeska b mnu mnu-w mnjar je shen'ka-w-n w jrga n
So he stayed with the snake.
Then the place looked nice, with flowers, and other nice things in the middle.
tgapanra b ram pek' juela mamaw k jir jir otro wa julur-g-n sa/ shann bi n
Then it seems that the parents came back home;
je (m) tgapa kaga-wa juela deu-lo-n j ska n
they got to the place where they had left the child asleep,
Kawu-lo-n m t yaba jatan kp ska ra
but the child was not sleeping there.
They got scared and went out with sticks, they searched for the child under the trees, the flowers, in the middle of the bush,
kaga-wa mleten'-w kawu-lo-n je-wa desu-lo j shebega kal ra beteu-lo-te-n kal dig jrgaten mamaw dig jrgaten k'yega jrgaten (m)
but they could not find him.
Yaba yul-n ka yaba kr ta
They made noise and then a wolf appeared before them;
Koyir-gate-n mga jeska se je t s-ra lobo bi n desu-n wm n (_)
they tried to scare it off; they thought it had devoured the child;
t mleche-g-n begets-ite je n t yaba kat-w r (_)
they hit it with sticks, but it was not that one that had devoured the child.
Jeb begte-ite k n kal wa (_) ka r je kuna Ka je w yaba katan-w kuna
The child had been taken away by something else; he was somewhere else.
Ta yaba mntse r kww dul-n r kwwn (_)
They did not know what to do or think or where to go;
Ta ultimo/ jeska wakwa ka inga juen mga jir mw-ite mga jir begetse-ite mga mnw mu-lo
who could have taken the child away?
Something must have devoured the child, or he might be lost, or dead.
yaba kat-w jir t r Ta yaba shen'-w r yaba d-w
There something else appeared that we call bear. It was big and black;
jeska mga otro tsnte-n r komo se she-ra r oso bi keyege n dolon n
it was holding the child in its hand; it was playing with the child in the middle of the flowers.
Je n t yaba gugcha-n jula jrga n Je kajki-n jin kww n yaba ra mamaw shajrgan
It was kissing and tickling him.
So they got very scared because the child was lost.
Jera jie-wa mletr-te t (_) Yaba shen'-w r
Who might have taken the child away?
There they were and there it ends.
(_) Jeska bi b wakwa dujali bi b jeska b n'-w
I dont know what and where took him away;
Jeska s-inga juen n jir mnu mga mntse w r
or whether they took care of him.
Jatan' bi (m) jera je t kunn-g-n bi (m)
Jebi b (m) kaga min mina-wa jatan'-tan je begets
And the place looked very nice.
